</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
/pet hold has absolutely nothing to do with keeping your pet on one mob.  Read the above descriptions for what it does.
<br />

<br />
Your pet is behaving exactly the same way as a mob behaves when its under attack - perhaps its similar to being 'stupid' (as, arguably mobs are stupid) but knowing this should help you in figuring out mob positioning.
<br />

<br />
The solution to your problem is to build up enough aggro on each of the Centiens so that they follow you (like .. one slow each) and bunch them all up.  On the pull you can pop BST defensive to make it less painful for you as you tank them all (if desired - easier to get aggro).  The position the whole bunch between you and pet (well thats my preference, it really doesn't matter at this point), with dual wield your push should be close to that of the pet and then the mobs will all stay together.  Occasionally /pet backoff /pet attack to make sure its attacking the right one.
<br />

<br />
And finally, pulling 3 centiens is nothing short of painful ... can you ever kill them if 2 of them are clerics?  Rellic doesn't interrupt their casting ... <img src="images/smiles/icon_eek.gif" alt="Shocked" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
