			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Pet hold means that if you're pulling you can bring along your pet rather than parking him at camp. Then if you proximity aggro a critter -- or foolishly stumble across an unexpected mob, your pet will jump to your defense, you can start to run back to camp, and with a /pet hold, your pet will happily jog along behind you with the mob hitting your pet INSTEAD of you.
<br />

<br />
Now for beastlords it's not quite as critical as for mages, but it's still nice. Pet hold is wonderful. With skillful use of /pet guard here and /pet guard me and /pet hold you can easily have your pet pull a mob closer to you if you're clericing, stay away from you and NOT attack through an enrage, pull a mob back to a guard spot, get out of the path of an oncoming add, reposition him around a mob easily, ignore mob AE... /sniff I miss not having pet hold with my beastlord yet.
<br />

<br />
I haven't heard anyone yet say that they regret spending the points on /pet hold. It's definitely high on my list of things to get.
<br />

<br />
Rippykin 59 Beastlord
<br />
Quellious</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
